    "They support the development of personalized, dialogic, and multimodal experiments; allow precise control over emotional and moral framing; and enable the study of socially sensitive content under ethical safeguards.",
    "Across the studies reviewed, LLMs have increased both the realism and flexibility of experimental methods while opening new possibilities for theory testing and design innovation.",
    "For communication researchers, this marks the emergence of a new experimental paradigm-one that is more responsive to the complexity of mediated human behavior in the digital era.",
    "4.2 Replicating Social Science Experiments with LLM-Simulated Agents An emerging trend in experimental research involves using LLMs to simulate human participants and replicate established social science experiments.",
    "Instead of recruiting human subjects, researchers prompt models such as GPT-4 or Claude 3.5 to adopt specific demographic profiles and cognitive roles."
